📦 Variables in Python
📌 What is a Variable?
A variable stores data.
name = "John"
age = 25

⚠️ Rules for Variables
Must start with letter or _
Cannot start with number
Case-sensitive
Cannot use keywords (if, class, def)
❌ Invalid Example
5age = 25  # Error

🎯 Naming Conventions
✔ Good Practice (snake_case)
user_age = 30
❌ Bad Practice
ua = 30
❌ Avoid single letters
x = 10

💬 Comments
# This is a comment
🖨️ print() Function

📌 What it does
Displays output.
print("Hello World")

📌 Multiple values
print("My colors are", "blue", "green", "red")
✔ Output adds spaces automatically
